Object.Field: insert into ctl_input_files_loading select * from CTL_INPUT_FILES where file_id in (select file_id from CTL_FILE_2_LOAD_2) and source_name='MCRM'
select nvl(max(file_id),-1) file_id from ( select file_id from CTL_INPUT_FILES_LOADING where status_cd='1' and source_name='MCRM' and rownum<=1 union all select null from dual )
select file_name from CTL_INPUT_FILES_LOADING where file_id=#VTBL.V_MCRM_FILE_ID
LOAD FILE '#VTBL.V_CRM_FILENAME' ON SCHEMA CRM DB_PROPS crm.properties INSERT_ONLY

merge into CTL_INPUT_FILES_LOADING t using ( SELECT distinct f.file_id, i.timestamp_, i.user_, i.entity, mo.MESSAGE_NO, mo.NAME, i.base FROM PRE_STG_XML_CRM.CRM_PACKAGE p left join PRE_STG_XML_CRM.CRM_DATA d on p.PACKAGEPK=d.PACKAGEFK left join ETL.CTL_INPUT_FILES f on f.FILE_NAME=p.SNPSFILEPATH||p.SNPSFILENAME left join PRE_STG_XML_CRM.CRM_INFO i on p.PACKAGEPK=i.PACKAGEFK left join PRE_STG_XML_CRM.CRM_METAOBJECTS m on m.infofk=i.infopk left join PRE_STG_XML_CRM.CRM_METAOBJECT mo on mo.metaobjectsfk=m.metaobjectspk where p.SNPSFILEPATH like '%CRM%' ) s on (t.file_id=s.file_id) when matched then update set t.timestamp#=to_date(replace(s.timestamp_,'T', ' '),'YYYY-MM-DD hh24:mi:ss'), t.user#=s.user_, t.entity=s.entity, t.meta_name=s.name, t.meta_MESSAGE_NO=s.MESSAGE_NO, t.base=s.base
